%pyspark

# define the data frame source on the given column selection only (we don't want to read the whole thing!)
df = spark.read.parquet("file:///data/gaia/dr2/*.parquet").select("source_id","parallax_error").where("parallax_error is not null")
# note also we have to exclude the null values resulting from 2-paramater astrometric solutions (this wasn't necessary in TGAS by definition)

# debug: physical execution plan and resulting schema
df.explain()
df.show()
df.schema

%pyspark

# create an RDD from the data frame
rdd = df.rdd
print ('RDD created from Data Frame has %d partitions by default' % (rdd.getNumPartitions()))

# map at HEALPix level 5
healpix_level_5 = rdd.map(lambda x: (x[0] >> 49, x[1])) 

# repartition the data (no partitioning function = default hash partitioner) - we cannot assume that all occurences of a given key are confined to one partition
# (this step would not be necessary if the data were partitioned by HEALPix at this level or higher)
repartitioned_rdd = healpix_level_5.partitionBy(64)
# for now match the number of partitions to the number of cores ... note that in Jan 2020 deployment this step takes 15 to 20 mins.

# debug:
values_per_key = repartitioned_rdd.map(lambda x: (x[0], 1)).reduceByKey(lambda a,b: a+b)
print("Number of unique keys in repartitioned RDD: ",values_per_key.count())
print("Number of partitions: ", repartitioned_rdd.getNumPartitions())
print(values_per_key.sample(False, 0.001).collect())
// from here just do as previously...

%pyspark

# remedian class
class Remedian():
    '''
    classdocs TODO
    '''
    
    # fixed buffer size must always be an odd integer in this implementation
    bufferSize = 11
    
    def __init__(self):
        '''
        Constructor.
        '''
        self.values = []
        self.numInArray = []
        self.numAccumulated = 0
        self.addNewList()
        self.merged = set()
        
    def add(self, value):
        self.append(value, 0)
        self.numAccumulated += 1
    
    def append(self, value, index):

        # convenience references
        array = self.values[index]
        num = self.numInArray[index]

        if num == self.bufferSize:
            
            # need to determine the median of this array
            array.sort()
            median = array[int(self.bufferSize / 2)]
            
            # create a new accumulation array if needed
            if len(self.values) - 1 == index: self.addNewList()
            
            # and append to the next array accumulation
            self.append(median, index + 1)
            num = 0
            self.numInArray[index] = num
            
        # finally add in the original new value
        array[num] = value
        self.numInArray[index] = num + 1
    
    def getMedian(self):
        
        # default if the method cannot return a valid resut
        value = float("nan")
        
        # get the lowest level array accumulation
        array = self.values[-1]
        n = self.numInArray[-1]
        
        # derive the median
        if n == 1:
            value = array[0]
        elif n > 1:
            # copy active elements and sort the array:
            copy = array[0:n]
            copy.sort()
            if n % 2 == 0:
                i = int(n/2) - 1
                value = (copy[i] + copy[i + 1]) / 2.0
            else:
                value = copy[int(n / 2)]
                
        return value
    
    def addNewList(self):
        
        # append new list of buffer length
        self.values.append([0.0] * self.bufferSize)
        self.numInArray.append(0)
    
    def getNumberAccumulated(self):
        return self.numAccumulated
        
# utility generator function for the class
from collections import defaultdict

def remedian(iterator):
    
    remedians = defaultdict(lambda: Remedian())
    for k,v in iterator: remedians[k].add(v)
        
    yield [(k, remedian.getMedian()) for k, remedian in remedians.items()]

%pyspark
result = repartitioned_rdd.mapPartitions(remedian).flatMap(lambda x: x).cache()
result.count()
# result count should be the same as the number of unique map keys (12288 level 5 HEALpixels)

%pyspark

# plot the results
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import healpy as hp

# healpy constants
NSIDE = 32
NPIX = hp.nside2npix(NSIDE)

# do the visualisation
array_like = np.empty(NPIX)
for item in result.collect(): array_like[item[0]] = item[1]
hp.mollview(array_like, nest=True, title="Median parallax uncertainty [mas]")
hp.graticule(coord="E", color="white")

%pyspark

# Some Apache Spark 101 stuff

rdd = df.rdd
print ('RDD created from Data Frame has %d partitions by default' % (rdd.getNumPartitions()))

# by default spark creates one partition per (default) block size of file storage. If this default is 128Mbyte, then 5985 partitions means a total data size of 766GB here.
# Jobs are then distributed across the available worker nodes in parallel, one partition per worker at a time, concurrently across the workers to achieve parallelism, 
# until the job has run over all the partitions

# row counts by partition:

from pyspark.sql.functions  import spark_partition_id
partition_info = df.withColumn("partitionId", spark_partition_id()).groupBy("partitionId").count()

# cache it in memory to make the subsequent cells speedy
partition_info.cache()

%pyspark
